Citations
Date:  0/0/1941
Source:  Dictionary of the Underworld
Author:  PARTRiDGE
Vol / Page:  322
Edition:  1961
Quote:  A criminal that works alone and is very secretive: Australian late C. 19-20. in, e.g., Morris, 1898; Partridge, 1938 Baker, 1942. Also hatting (-1890): such a way of working and living. Ex the Australians. hatter, a miner working and living alone: he may go as mad as a hatter.
